[Tkacik] <i>Les Wexner</i>
<i>has been embroiled in scandals.</i>

1466
01:19:41.485 --> 01:19:43.653
Just heading to a meeting. Thank you.

1467
01:19:44.196 --> 01:19:47.991
[reporter 6] <i>Les Wexner announced</i>
<i>he was stepping down as CEO of L Brands.</i>

1468
01:19:49.534 --> 01:19:53.705
[reporter 7] <i>He remains under scrutiny</i>
<i>for his close ties to Jeffrey Epstein.</i>

1469
01:19:53.789 --> 01:19:57.167
<i>the convicted sex offender</i>
<i>and disgraced financier.</i>

1470
01:19:57.667 --> 01:20:00.796
[Tkacik] He not only signed over
his entire fortune to Jeffrey Epstein.

1471
01:20:00.879 --> 01:20:04.841
he let Jeffrey represent himself
as a Victoria's Secret model scout.

1472
01:20:06.218 --> 01:20:07.969
One of the biggest reasons

1473
01:20:08.053 --> 01:20:11.765
Jeffrey Epstein was able
to surround himself constantly

1474
01:20:11.848 --> 01:20:14.142
with really hot young women.

1475
01:20:14.226 --> 01:20:17.604
they thought that he could.
you know. make or break them.

1476
01:20:17.687 --> 01:20:20.690
Bombshell exposé in <i>The New York Times.</i>

1477
01:20:20.774 --> 01:20:24.402
Bruce Weber guilty of years
of sexual misconduct and abuse.

1478
01:20:25.487 --> 01:20:28.907
[Tkacik] <i>Bruce Weber. of course.</i>
<i>would be sued by legions of models.</i>

1479
01:20:29.658 --> 01:20:33.495
Bruce told me I was tense
and did some breathing exercises with me.

1480
01:20:33.995 --> 01:20:35.705
At the time. I froze.

1481
01:20:35.789 --> 01:20:37.624
I did not know how to respond.

1482
01:20:37.707 --> 01:20:41.253
The entire experience
was terrifying and humiliating.

1483
01:21:06.903 --> 01:21:12.826
Changes tend to happen when. you know.
those who raise concerns can point out

1484
01:21:12.909 --> 01:21:16.413
all the ways in which a company
is leaving money on a table

1485
01:21:16.496 --> 01:21:18.582
by its current actions.

1486
01:21:18.665 --> 01:21:20.166
And then changes happen.

1487
01:21:20.834 --> 01:21:24.337
Repositioning a brand<i> </i>and moving
a brand forward is not always easy.

1488
01:21:24.421 --> 01:21:27.424
So. candidly. we've had
a few starts and stops on our journey.

1489
01:21:27.507 --> 01:21:30.218
We are no longer the company
that we used to be.

1490
01:21:30.302 --> 01:21:32.345
That we could wipe clean
our social channels.

1491
01:21:32.429 --> 01:21:34.389
wipe clean the history.

1492
01:21:52.365 --> 01:21:54.743
[Lindsey] Having a broad range
of people represented

1493
01:21:54.826 --> 01:21:58.997
and feel included in your brand
is smart business.

1494
01:21:59.080 --> 01:22:01.708
There <i>is </i>a smart business
of being discriminatory

1495
01:22:01.791 --> 01:22:04.669
and being exclusionary.
because there are always gonna be people

1496
01:22:04.753 --> 01:22:07.797
who want to see themselves
as the cool kids.

1497
01:22:07.881 --> 01:22:10.508
But it's fascinating to see
how many brands now

1498
01:22:10.592 --> 01:22:14.387
are doubling down on the cool kids
being anybody and everybody.

1499
01:22:15.889 --> 01:22:19.976
And they've gone the other direction
with respect to the diversity of models.

1500
01:22:20.060 --> 01:22:22.562
Abercrombie & Fitch has announced plans

1501
01:22:22.646 --> 01:22:26.316
to no longer hire employees
based on attractiveness.

1502
01:22:26.399 --> 01:22:29.986
which should make
the first new guy they hire feel great.

1503
01:22:30.070 --> 01:22:31.571
[audience laughter]

1504
01:22:31.655 --> 01:22:34.699
It's just a shame
that we couldn't have gone to that sooner.

1505
01:22:37.118 --> 01:22:41.331
Abercrombie & Fitch is illustrative
more so than it is exceptional.

1506
01:22:41.957 --> 01:22:45.961
[Rupp] <i>They didn't invent evil.</i>
<i>They didn't invent class.</i>

1507
01:22:46.044 --> 01:22:48.129
<i>They just packaged it.</i>

1508
01:22:48.213 --> 01:22:52.384
If anything. it represents
the worst parts of American history

1509
01:22:52.467 --> 01:22:56.096
in terms of the cost.
the hiring practices. the images.

1510
01:22:56.179 --> 01:22:59.891
It's everything we want America not to be.

1511
01:23:00.684 --> 01:23:02.936
[Rupp] We all like to think
we have grown beyond that.

1512
01:23:03.019 --> 01:23:04.896
that we're all a little bit better.

1513
01:23:06.439 --> 01:23:10.402
I don't know what it says about us
that it was so popular for so long.

1514
01:23:10.485 --> 01:23:11.319
Probably

1515
01:23:12.487 --> 01:23:15.365
that we really wanted to be liked.
[laughs]

1516
01:23:15.448 --> 01:23:20.787
We were kind of.
you know. blinded by our own… light.

1517
01:23:20.870 --> 01:23:23.581
[laughs] You know. we were like.
"We're so great. We're so successful."

1518
01:23:23.665 --> 01:23:26.334
But. like. social media wasn't a thing.

1519
01:23:26.418 --> 01:23:29.963
There were probably
just as many people as there are now

1520
01:23:30.046 --> 01:23:32.674
who hated what we were doing.
who were completely offended.

1521
01:23:32.757 --> 01:23:35.885
who didn't feel included.
who didn't feel represented.

1522
01:23:35.969 --> 01:23:38.596
But they didn't have the platform
to be able to voice it.

1523
01:23:38.680 --> 01:23:40.390
and now they do. so maybe…

1524
01:23:40.473 --> 01:23:43.476
Yeah. maybe it's not. like.
this massive societal new awareness.

1525
01:23:43.560 --> 01:23:47.605
It's just now we're hearing everyone.
and we have to pay attention.

1526
01:23:50.275 --> 01:23:55.238
[Yu] I think there's a limitation
to where brands can really walk the walk.

1527
01:23:55.321 --> 01:23:58.575
When it really comes down to it.
you're trying to sell something. right?

1528
01:23:58.658 --> 01:24:01.578
Can you really sell diversity inclusion

1529
01:24:01.661 --> 01:24:05.165
when really what you're trying to sell
is a V-neck. you know?

1530
01:24:05.999 --> 01:24:08.710
[Ocampo] My hope is that companies realize
that they play

1531
01:24:08.793 --> 01:24:12.922
a pivotal role in shaping culture.
shaping conversations.

1532
01:24:13.006 --> 01:24:17.177
shaping which people
in this society are valued.

1533
01:24:17.260 --> 01:24:20.680
The story of Abercrombie
is essentially an incredible indictment

1534
01:24:20.764 --> 01:24:22.932
of where our culture was…

1535
01:24:24.517 --> 01:24:26.227
oh. just ten years ago.

1536
01:24:26.311 --> 01:24:31.900
It was a culture
that. um. enthusiastically embraced

1537
01:24:31.983 --> 01:24:37.530
a nearly all sort of WASPy vision
of the world.

1538
01:24:37.614 --> 01:24:43.953
It was a culture that defined beauty
as thin and white and young.

1539
01:24:44.037 --> 01:24:50.335
and it was a culture
that was very happy to exclude people.

1540
